Shakespeare, as people reminded each other, wrote King Lear when he was quarantined during a plague.
Just a reminder that when Shakespeare was quarantined because of the plague, he wrote King Lear.
“I, too, am declining to write the next King Lear as protest against capitalism,” proclaimed Rosa Lyster at the Outline.
I just stared in a blank fury at that Rosanne Cash tweet reminding me that Shakespeare wrote King Lear during quarantine.
“We’re already dealing with a global emergency and now I’m supposed to write King Lear on top of that?